25|$|The CRA {{followed}} similar laws {{passed to}} reduce {{discrimination in the}} credit and housing markets including the Fair Housing Act of 1968, the Equal Credit Opportunity Act of 1974 and the <b>Home</b> <b>Mortgage</b> Disclosure Act of 1975 (HMDA). The Fair Housing Act and the Equal Credit Opportunity Act prohibit {{discrimination on the basis}} of race, sex, or other personal characteristics. The <b>Home</b> <b>Mortgage</b> Disclosure Act requires that financial institutions publicly disclose mortgage lending and application data. In contrast with those acts, the CRA seeks to ensure the provision of credit to all parts of a community, regardless of the relative wealth or poverty of a neighborhood.|$|E
